Package com.irurueta.navigation.inertial

Class ECEFKinematics

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.irurueta.navigation.inertial.ECIorECEFKinematics<ECEFKinematics>
      • com.irurueta.navigation.inertial.ECEFKinematics
  • public class ECEFKinematics
extends ECIorECEFKinematics<ECEFKinematics>
    Describes the motion of a body based on the specific forces (i.e. specific accelerations) and angular rates applied to it with respect the ECEF frame and resolved along body-frame axes. Body frame axes are typically defined so that x is the forward axis, pointing in the usual direction of travel, z is the down axis, pointing in the usual direction of gravity, and y is the right axis, completing the orthogonal set.
